  "prompt": "What is a bank branch name?",
  "response": "A bank branch name refers to the specific name of a physical location of a bank where customers can conduct financial transactions and access banking services. Each branch of a bank is typically identified by a unique name, often based on its location, such as \"Main Street Branch,\" \"Downtown Branch,\" or \"Midtown Branch.\" The branch name helps distinguish one location from another within the same bank's network. It may also include the bank's name to clearly indicate which financial institution it belongs to, for example, \"Bank of America - Central Plaza Branch\" or \"Chase Bank - Westside Branch.\" The branch name is important for directing customers to the correct location for their banking needs.",
